(5632, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/so-simple-a-free-minimalist-wordpress-theme-from-press75?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=so-simple-a-free-minimalist-wordpress-theme-from-press75'' title=''Last week the big news in the world of WordPress themes was Westwerk’s acquisition of Press75, one of the oldest theme shops originally founded by Jason Schuller in 2008. The folks at Westwerk began implementing changes immediately and announced new pricing options the same day the shop’s new owner was introduced. Single theme purchases are now back in the m [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: So Simple: A Free Minimalist WordPress Theme from Press75</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/wordpress-multi-environment-config-work-seamlessly-between-development-staging-and-production-sites?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=wordpress-multi-environment-config-work-seamlessly-between-development-staging-and-production-sites'' title=''photo credit: Matteo Bagnoli – cc WordPress doesn’t have built-in support for developers working in multiple environments, i.e. local, staging, and production. It’s no surprise, given that this workflow isn’t part of the vast majority of users’ lives when publishing with WordPress. Nevertheless, running a separate development site can be a complex and tediou [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: WordPress Multi-Environment Config: Work Seamlessly Between Development, Staging, and Production Sites</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2014/06/09/erick-arbe-wordpress-navigation-in-responsive-design-2/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Erick Arbé: WordPress Navigation in Responsive Design</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2014/06/09/manuel-schmalstieg-date-management-for-minimalists/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Manuel Schmalstieg: Date Management for Minimalists</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2014/06/09/andrea-middleton-a-world-of-wordcamps/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Andrea Middleton: A World of WordCamps</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
